						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Climate-change/Related-developments/Free-interactive-access-to-open-weather-data-through-aWhere" title="Free, interactive access to open weather data through aWhere" alt="link">Free, interactive access to open weather data through aWhere</a></h2>

	
					<p>aWhere’s location intelligence platform enables integration of complex agricultural, environmental and public health data into local, actionable insight. A SaaS (Software as a service) business, aWhere’s platform currently offers free (after simple registration) access to weather data. It will expand by creating an interactive on-stop-shop to analyse, visualise and compare openly available data through charts, maps and tables. A comprehensive data library, which is being compiled from a variety of open data sources (FAO, USAID, among others) will allow for an in depth analysis of weather data. &nbsp;(<a href="http://www.awhere.com/en-us/awherehome?utm_source=K4DNewsletterEN&amp;utm_medium=Link&amp;utm_campaign=K4D_EN_May2013" target="_self">aWhere</a>, 2013)</p>
							<p><span class="date">2/07/2013</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Climate-change/Related-developments/Free-interactive-access-to-open-weather-data-through-aWhere">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
