						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Climate-change/Related-developments/Growing-peas-and-greens-to-maximise-water-usage" title="Growing peas and greens to maximise water usage " alt="link">Growing peas and greens to maximise water usage </a></h2>

	
					<p>IPS reports how Kenyan farmers save water by planting crops that require little irrigation, unlike the popular maize. Indigenous vegetables and fruits such as the spider plant and the African nightshade are making a comeback on smallholder farms. Because these plants mature faster than conventional crops they can adapt more rapidly to climate variations.(<a href="http://www.ipsnews.net/2013/05/eating-peas-and-greens-to-maximise-water-usage/" target="_blank">IPS</a>, 22/05/2013)</p>
							<p><span class="date">27/06/2013</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Climate-change/Related-developments/Growing-peas-and-greens-to-maximise-water-usage">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
