						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Climate-change/Related-developments/Cultural-practices-to-maintain-soil-quality-and-address-climate-change" title="Cultural practices to maintain soil quality and address climate change" alt="link">Cultural practices to maintain soil quality and address climate change</a></h2>

	
					<p>To keep soils productive and reduce their climate change footprint, farmers in the USA are encouraged to graze sheep more readily, adopt no-till systems, rotate crops, and use less nitrogen fertiliser.<a href="http://www.ars.usda.gov/is/AR/archive/mar13/soil0313.htm" target="_self">http://www.ars.usda.gov/is/AR/archive/mar13/soil0313.htm</a>(USDA Agricultural Research Service, 8/03/2013)</p>
